article.description: — Bentiu Panoam scored 19 points as North Dakota beat Nebraska Omaha 81-69 on Saturday night. Filip Rebraca added 17 points for the Fighting Hawks, while Ethan Igbanugo chipped in 16.
article.headline: Panoam, Rebraca carry North Dakota over Omaha 81-69
article.linkText: Panoam, Rebraca carry North Dakota over Omaha 81-69
article.story: OMAHA, Neb. -- — Bentiu Panoam scored 19 points as North Dakota beat Nebraska Omaha 81-69 on Saturday night. Filip Rebraca added 17 points for the Fighting Hawks, while Ethan Igbanugo chipped in 16. Panoam shot 5 for 7 from behind the arc. Rebraca also had 13 rebounds. Tyree Ihenacho had nine points, 12 rebounds and six assists for North Dakota (9-16, 9-10 Summit League). Matt Pile had 16 points for the Mavericks (3-19, 1-11). Ayo Akinwole added 16 points. Jadin Booth had 12 points. The Fighting Hawks evened the season series against the Mavericks with the win. Nebraska Omaha defeated North Dakota 72-62 on Friday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
